        </param>
        <param>
          <type>bool</type>
          <declname>last_click_only</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="group___clicks_1ga9a923c600f6774d9858ae96b57d308a6" kindref="member">ClickHandler</ref></type>
          <declname>handler</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Subscribe to multi click events. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Must be called from the <ref refid="group___clicks_1gaac872430f49a1bee56078e7b1f4a202a" kindref="member">ClickConfigProvider</ref>. </para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>button_id</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The button events to subscribe to. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>min_clicks</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Minimum number of clicks before handler is fired. Defaults to 2. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>max_clicks</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Maximum number of clicks after which the click counter is reset. A value of 0 means use &quot;min&quot; also as &quot;max&quot;. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>timeout</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The delay after which a sequence of clicks is considered finished, and the click counter is reset. A value of 0 means to use the system default 300ms. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>last_click_only</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Defaults to false. When true, only the handler for the last multi-click is called. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>handler</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The <ref refid="group___clicks_1ga9a923c600f6774d9858ae96b57d308a6" kindref="member">ClickHandler</ref> to fire on this event. Fired for multi-clicks, as &quot;filtered&quot; by the <computeroutput>last_click_only</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>min</computeroutput>, and <computeroutput>max</computeroutput> parameters. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
